The paper discusses data quality challenges in a security incident response team, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the need for data validation and recording in relevant datastores, which relates to database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents a case study and discusses the foundation for future research, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
